Subject: [PATCH 11/19] =?UTF-8?q?feat:=20audit=20OIDC/OAuth2=20callback=20?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=E2=80=94=20track=20AUTH=5FOIDC=5FLOGIN=20and=20=5FFAIL=20in=20?=
 =?UTF-8?q?NIS2=20access=20log?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Add action rules for the OIDC/OAuth2 callback endpoints to the access
log middleware so that every federated login attempt (success and
failure) is captured in the structured NIS2-compliant audit trail.

Changes in backend/open_webui/middleware/access_log.py:
- Add three regex rules mapping the OIDC callback GET paths to the new
  action type AUTH_OIDC_LOGIN:
    GET /oauth/{provider}/login/callback  (current path)
    GET /oauth/{provider}/callback        (legacy alias)
    GET /oauth/clients/{client_id}/callback (dynamic OAuth clients)
- Add AUTH_OIDC_LOGIN to _NIS2_SECURITY_ACTIONS so every OIDC login is
  emitted at WARNING level for SIEM / Log360 ingestion.
- Extend the _FAIL detection block to include AUTH_OIDC_LOGIN: a 4xx
  response on the callback URL produces action=AUTH_OIDC_LOGIN_FAIL
  with nis2=Y, enabling brute-force detection in Log360 UEBA.

Before this fix a failed OIDC login appeared as:
  action=-  outcome=failure  nis2=N
After:
  action=AUTH_OIDC_LOGIN_FAIL  outcome=failure  nis2=Y  (WARNING level)

Note: OIDC claims returned by the IdP on failure (sub, email, roles,
groups) continue to be logged by oauth.py at WARNING level and are
visible by grepping 'OAuth callback failed' in the application log.

Co-authored-by: Copilot <223556219+Copilot@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 backend/open_webui/middleware/access_log.py | 10 ++++++++--
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/backend/open_webui/middleware/access_log.py b/backend/open_webui/middleware/access_log.py
index e9ae765af..b4f929664 100644
--- a/backend/open_webui/middleware/access_log.py
+++ b/backend/open_webui/middleware/access_log.py
@@ -86,6 +86,7 @@ Log format example
 NIS2 Action Categories
 -----------------------
   AUTH_*       — Authentication & session lifecycle
+                 AUTH_OIDC_LOGIN       — OIDC/OAuth2 callback (success=302, fail=4xx → _FAIL)
   USER_*       — User account management
   GROUP_*      — Group & membership management
   CONFIG_*     — System configuration changes
@@ -192,6 +193,10 @@ def _compile_action_rules() -> list[tuple[re.Pattern, Optional[str], str]]:
         (rf"^/api/v1/auths/api_key$", "POST", "AUTH_API_KEY_CREATE"),
         (rf"^/api/v1/auths/api_key$", "DELETE", "AUTH_API_KEY_DELETE"),
         (rf"^/api/v1/auths/oauth/{_ID}/token/exchange$", "POST", "AUTH_OAUTH_TOKEN"),
+        # OIDC/OAuth2 callback endpoints (GET — browser redirect after IdP authentication)
+        (rf"^/oauth/{_ID}/login/callback$", "GET", "AUTH_OIDC_LOGIN"),
+        (rf"^/oauth/{_ID}/callback$", "GET", "AUTH_OIDC_LOGIN"),        # legacy path
+        (rf"^/oauth/clients/{_ID}/callback$", "GET", "AUTH_OIDC_LOGIN"), # dynamic OAuth clients
         (rf"^/api/v1/auths/admin/config/ldap/server$", "POST", "CONFIG_LDAP_SERVER"),
         (rf"^/api/v1/auths/admin/config/ldap$", "POST", "CONFIG_LDAP"),
         (rf"^/api/v1/auths/admin/config$", "POST", "CONFIG_AUTH"),
@@ -385,7 +390,7 @@ _NIS2_SECURITY_ACTIONS = frozenset({
     # Authentication
     "AUTH_LOGIN", "AUTH_LOGIN_LDAP", "AUTH_SIGNUP", "AUTH_LOGOUT",
     "AUTH_PASSWORD_CHANGE", "AUTH_API_KEY_CREATE", "AUTH_API_KEY_DELETE",
-    "AUTH_OAUTH_TOKEN",
+    "AUTH_OAUTH_TOKEN", "AUTH_OIDC_LOGIN",
     # User management
     "USER_CREATE", "USER_UPDATE", "USER_DELETE", "USER_PERMISSIONS_DEFAULT",
     # Group management
@@ -811,7 +816,8 @@ class AccessLogMiddleware(BaseHTTPMiddleware):
         outcome = _outcome_from_status(status_code)
 
         # Detect failed auth attempts (NIS2 Art.21 — incident detection)
-        if action_type in ("AUTH_LOGIN", "AUTH_LOGIN_LDAP", "AUTH_SIGNUP") and status_code >= 400:
+        # AUTH_OIDC_LOGIN: success = 302 redirect to app; failure = 4xx
+        if action_type in ("AUTH_LOGIN", "AUTH_LOGIN_LDAP", "AUTH_SIGNUP", "AUTH_OIDC_LOGIN") and status_code >= 400:
             effective_action = f"{action_type}_FAIL"
             effective_nis2 = True
         else:
